cs.AR, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.ET 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-categories of cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.ET (Embedded Systems). 

The paper proposes a hardware accelerator for CNNs that focuses on exploiting sparsity and reduced precision for both training and inference. This makes it relevant to cs.AR, which deals with hardware architecture, and cs.ET, which deals with embedded systems. The use of CNNs for computer vision applications makes it relevant to cs.CV. The focus on sparsity and reduced precision for training and inference makes it relevant to cs.NE. Finally, the use of efficient memory interfaces and algorithms for CNN evaluation makes it relevant to cs.SY.
